China's most powerful and efficient F-class #GasTurbine M701F5 rolled off production line on Tue in SW China's Sichuan. The machine will serve a power plant that can generate 3.266 bln kWh of electricity per year while saving 100 mln m3 of #NaturalGas in S China's Guangdong. https://t.co/u7F5gM46wV

China's homegrown latest-generation offshore #WindPower installation platform, Huaxi 1600, was delivered Thur in E China's Qingdao. The 136-m-long and 50-m-wide self-propelled jack-up platform weighs 1,600t and is by far the most versatile & efficient of its kind. #MadeinChina https://t.co/V71K5JS5ro

China's 1st high-power #electric shunting locomotive rolled off the production line Thur in Zhuzhou, C China's Hunan. With a maximum towing power of 1,500 kW, this #locomotive designed for industrial users can travel 128 km while hauling 1,200 tonnes of cargo on a full charge. https://t.co/nFX3kHFxGz

China's Minister of Commerce Wang Wentao will hold talks with US Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo during the #APEC Economic Leaders' Meeting.

The two sides will discuss the implementation of the consensus reached by the two heads of state at their summit in San Francisco and resolve important issues in bilateral economic and trade relations, a MOC spokesperson said on Thursday.  #APEC2023
